<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 2:16PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Madison
and central Beaverhead Counties through 300 PM MDT...
At 216 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Dillon, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dillon, Beaverhead Rock State Park, Clark Canyon and Glen.
This includes Interstate 15 between mile markers 44  and 83 , and
between mile markers 85  and 87 .
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
